# NOTAM Intelligence Project Rules

You are working on NOTAM Intelligence, a global AI-powered pre-flight briefing platform.

## Always
- Read CLAUDE.md first for full project context
- Push to GitHub after every change
- Use inline CSS only (no frameworks)
- Keep dark aviation theme (#060a0f background, #4a9eff primary)
- Test sidebar-open and sidebar-collapsed states
- Use Claude Haiku for cheap operations, Sonnet for main briefing only

## Never
- Use position:fixed inside slide-in panels
- Add external CSS frameworks or libraries (except already loaded ones)
- Break the sidebar layout
- Remove existing console.log for CACHE/FILTER monitoring
- Use React, Vue, or any JS framework

## File Structure
- index.html — entire frontend SPA (large file, be careful with edits)
- server.js — Node.js backend
- All other .html files — static pages

## When Making Changes
1. grep first to find exact location before editing
2. Make minimal targeted changes
3. Always push to GitHub
4. Render auto-deploys from main branch
